  "text": "The results for services firms are more nuanced and indicate that while exporters and firms undertaking outward FDI are more productive than domestically oriented firms there is no significant difference in productivity between these two types of firms. Despite this, average productivity and point estimates from the regression analysis suggest that the productivity of exporting firms is larger than that for firms undertaking outward (albeit not significantly so), which provides partial support for the hypothesis of [CITATION_1] . Such results again hold across most quantiles, though the degree of heterogeneity across quantiles suggests that further work identifying the sources of such differences could be useful.",
